  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0dc5\u0db8\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 14\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da9\u0dca \u0d86\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dad \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "14 million American children are infected with Covid",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the latest report from the American Academy of Pediatrics (AAP) and the Children's Hospital Association, more than 14 million children in the United States have tested positive for Covid-19 since the start of the pandemic.",
        "About 92,000 children infected with Covid-19 were reported in the week ending July 21, which is the second consecutive weekly increase in reported cases, according to the report.",
        "\"New pediatric cases have decreased significantly since Omicron's peak, but this number is still significantly higher than the 39,000 pediatric cases reported a year ago on July 22, 2021,\" the AAP said.",
        "More than 311,000 cases of pediatric Covid-19 have been reported in the past four weeks in the United States, bringing the number of reported cases to 6.1 million in 2022.",
        "\"There is an urgent need to collect more age-specific data to assess disease severity as well as long-term effects associated with new variants,\" the AAP says.",
        "\"It is important to recognize the immediate effects of the pandemic on children's health, but just as importantly we need to recognize and address the long-term effects on the physical, mental and social well-being of these children and young people.\" It is further said.",
        "According to data from Johns Hopkins University, the total number of Covid-19 cases in the United States surpassed 90 million last Wednesday, with more than one million deaths.",
        "The United States is still at the forefront as the country worst affected by the epidemic with the highest number of cases and deaths in the world."
      ],
